Reasoning: The paper discusses the optimization of wireless networks, specifically the coexistence of new and legacy cellular networks in the next generation of wireless networks (5G). This involves the use of different waveforms, such as OFDM/OQAM and CP-OFDM, and the analysis of cross-interference between them. This topic falls under several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Communications (cs.COMM), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Multimedia (cs.MM).
